<dl id="n03009e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03009e">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03009e"> 9(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ Breastplate of SP <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n03009e"><li>FW 231.24 </li><li><a href="../../flex/kb/lexkb.htm#n03009e">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/kb/l39kb.htm#n03009e">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n03009e">MS missing</ms> </li><li>JJA not reproduced <a name="kad4" href="../../FF/fdra/kda.htm#kbd2">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/kb/kbd2.htm#n03009e">Draft: II.1&sect;2.2</a> </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: Entered by <a name="sh1007m" href="sh1all.htm#sh1007m">Sheet i-7(m)</a> </mm> <blockquote class="sources"> On Easter Sunday St. Patrick went to Tara with his companions to receive audience of the King in his Hall of Justice. As he went along he chanted the beautiful hymn, which has become known as the &lsquo;<mark>Breastplate of St. Patrick</mark>,&rsquo; in order to protect himself and his followers from the dangers by which they were encompassed. <small> J.M. Flood, <a name="JMFI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JMFI"><cite title="source">Ireland: Its Saints and Scholars</cite></a> (n.d) 13</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also: <a name="n03087c" href="n03all.htm#n03087c">N03 (VI.B.3):087(c)</a> </mm> </dd></dl>
